The paper deals with trajectory estimation using Gaussian process regression, which is a machine learning technique falling under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem is applied to a mobile robot dataset, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with stochastic differential equations, which are commonly used in control systems, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the possibility of using different vehicle dynamics models, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with simultaneous trajectory estimation and mapping, which is a common problem in computer vision, indicating that it falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
